description:
Degas
Harry N. Abrams | 1991 | ISBN: 0810981076 | English | 284 pages | PDF | 48 MB

The authors of Abrams' highly successful Monet and The Last Flowers of Manet have made the definitive book on the French Impressionist Edgar Degas. The New York Observer said, In the wonderfully readable text . . . we are put in very intimate touch with the artist's own sensibility. . . . This is a book not to be missed. 324 illustrations, 121 in full color. 2 gatefolds
